My favourite Brazilian wild cats:

  1. Pampa’s cat (Leopardus colocola) Wikipedia


  2. ocelot (Leopardus pardalis) Wikipedia


  3. margay (Leopardus wiedii) Wikipedia


  4. oncilla (Leopardus tigrinus) Wikipedia


  5. southern tiger cat (Leopardus guttulus) Wikipedia


  6. Geoffroy’s cat (Leopardus geoffroyi) Wikipedia


  7. jaguarundi (Herpailurus yagouaroundi) Wikipedia


I am a bit biased towards the Pampa’s cat… because of its distribution range!

There is ongoing debate of whether the species is actually a group of 3 different species or 1 species with 7 subspecies. According to the most updated studies from 2017, the subspecies L. c. pajeros is the one occurring in the Pampa grasslands of Rio Grande do Sul in Southern Brazil, where I come from!
